---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const components = [
  {
    name: 'PyProbe',
    repo: 'PyProbe',
    layer: 'L00',
    status: 'active',
    purpose: 'Memory pinning anchor',
    problem: "Python's memory model is fundamentally incompatible with zero-copy sharing. The GC moves objects, the allocator promotes/demotes memory, and the GIL makes even reading from another thread unsafe.",
    solution: 'A research-grade toolkit that pins Python objects to fixed addresses by directly reading CPython internals via ctypes. Uses PyObject_HEAD to get type info, traverses PyDictObject internals, and validates addresses before dereferencing.',
    statusDetails: {
      xray: { status: 'complete', desc: 'Read-only introspection of int, float, str, bytes, list, tuple, dict, set with cycle detection' },
      scalpel: { status: 'in_progress', desc: 'Controlled mutation with safety guarantees (refcount checks, interning detection)' },
      toolkit: { status: 'future', desc: 'Shared memory IPC, memory-mapped objects, hot-patching' }
    },
    keyInsight: 'CPython 3.12+ changed dict implementation from "compact" to split arrays. Had to decipher ma_keys, ma_values, dk_nentries, and tombstone detection.',
    code: `import pyprobe

data = {"name": "Alice", "age": 30}
ptr = pyprobe.pin(data)
result = ptr.xray()  # {'name': 'Alice', 'age': 30}`
  },
  {
    name: 'PyJX',
    repo: 'PyJx',
    layer: 'L02',
    status: 'active',
    purpose: 'Java-Python FFI bridge',
    problem: 'How do you make Python and Java talk without JNI overhead? How do you pass memory between runtimes without copying bytes through the kernel stack?',
    solution: 'A Python library that wraps Java classes as Python objects. Uses PyProbe to get stable pointers, then exposes them to Java through a clean Pythonic API. No glue code, no header files.',
    statusDetails: {
      wrapper: { status: 'complete', desc: 'Import Java classes directly: from pyjni.imports import MathUtils' },
      memory: { status: 'alpha', desc: 'Stable pointers via PyProbe integration' },
      panama: { status: 'planned', desc: 'Java 25 Project Panama integration for native memory' }
    },
    keyInsight: 'Unlike JNI, PyJX avoids native code entirely. It uses JPype-style approach but with PyProbe underneath for memory stability.',
    code: `from pyjni.imports import MathUtils

result = MathUtils.add(2, 3)  # Calls Java internally
print(result)  # 5`
  },
  {
    name: 'Nexus',
    repo: 'Nexus',
    layer: 'L03',
    status: 'active',
    purpose: 'FFI bridge via Project Panama',
    problem: "Java 25's Panama API is powerful but sprawling. MemorySegment, Arena, SymbolLookup, Linker, FunctionDescriptor - they all interact in ways documentation doesn't explain.",
    solution: 'Java 25 application using Project Panama (FFM API) to allocate native memory without JNI, expose memory to other runtimes via shared pointers, and handle lifecycle of buffers across language boundaries.',
    statusDetails: {
      arena: { status: 'complete', desc: 'Arena.ofShared() for native memory allocation' },
      struct: { status: 'complete', desc: 'MemoryLayout for C struct definitions' },
      native: { status: 'complete', desc: 'Simple native function calls (tested with printf)' },
      python: { status: 'blocked', desc: 'Cross-runtime boundary memory sharing - the wall being hit' }
    },
    keyInsight: 'The new architecture delegates to PyJX for Python objects. Panama handles native memory, not CPython internals. Nexus is now a specialist, not the spine.',
    code: `try (Arena arena = Arena.ofShared()) {
    MemorySegment buffer = arena.allocate(1024);
    long address = buffer.address();
    // Send 'address' to Python/Rust - zero copy
}`
  }
];

const layers = [
  { range: 'L11-L10', name: 'Human Intent', color: '#ff3366', components: ['Governance', 'Persona'] },
  { range: 'L09-L07', name: 'Cognition', color: '#a855f7', components: ['Medic (Elixir)', 'Logic (Haskell)', 'Temporal'] },
  { range: 'L06-L05', name: 'Decision', color: '#ffaa00', components: ['Dispatcher (Go)', 'Scientist (Julia)', 'Researcher (Python)'] },
  { range: 'L04-L01', name: 'Execution', color: '#00ff88', components: ['Guard (Rust)', 'Nexus (Java)', 'Mechanic (C)'] }
];

const flowSteps = [
  { step: 1, from: 'Python', to: 'PyProbe', desc: 'Pin object to fixed address' },
  { step: 2, from: 'PyProbe', to: 'PyJX', desc: 'Get stable memory pointer' },
  { step: 3, from: 'PyJX', to: 'Nexus', desc: 'Expose to Java via wrapper' },
  { step: 4, from: 'Nexus', to: 'Native', desc: 'Zero-copy via Panama Arena' }
];
---

<Layout title="Architecture" description="Deep dive into COBALT's 11-layer architecture. Why these problems exist and how we solve them with 9 specialized languages.">
  <article class="arch-page">
    <header class="arch-header">
      <h1 class="title">
        <span class="bracket">[</span> ARCHITECTURE <span class="bracket">]</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Why these problems exist and how we solve them</p>
    </header>

    <section class="intro">
      <div class="intro-card">
        <h2>The Core Problem</h2>
        <p>Every stack hits the same wall: <strong>you're using the wrong tool for the job</strong>. AR systems are slow, bloated, and built by people who've never had to optimize past <code>pip install</code>.</p>
        <p>COBALT's answer: an 11-layer system where <strong>every layer uses the tool that was made for its job</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="layers-vis">
      <h2 class="section-title">The Layer Stack</h2>
      <div class="layers-stack">
        {layers.map(l => (
          <div class="layer-block" style={`border-left-color: ${l.color}`}>
            <span class="layer-range">{l.range}</span>
            <span class="layer-name">{l.name}</span>
            <div class="layer-comps">
              {l.components.map(c => <span class="comp-tag">{c}</span>)}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="flow-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Data Flow: Python → Java → Native</h2>
      <div class="flow-diagram">
        {flowSteps.map(f => (
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="step-num">{f.step}</span>
            <span class="step-from">{f.from}</span>
            <span class="step-arrow">→</span>
            <span class="step-to">{f.to}</span>
            <span class="step-desc">{f.desc}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    {components.map(comp => (
      <section class="component-section">
        <div class="comp-header">
          <div class="comp-title">
            <h2>{comp.name}</h2>
            <span class="layer-badge">Layer {comp.layer}</span>
            <span class={`status-badge ${comp.status}`}>{comp.status}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="comp-purpose"><strong>Purpose:</strong> {comp.purpose}</p>
        </div>

        <div class="comp-body">
          <div class="problem-box">
            <h3>❌ The Problem</h3>
            <p>{comp.problem}</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="solution-box">
            <h3>✅ The Solution</h3>
            <p>{comp.solution}</p>
          </div>

          <div class="insight-box">
            <h3>💡 Key Insight</h3>
            <p>{comp.keyInsight}</p>
          </div>

          <div class="code-box">
            <h3>⟨/⟩ Code</h3>
            <pre><code>{comp.code}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="status-grid">
            {Object.entries(comp.statusDetails).map(([key, val]) => (
              <div class={`status-item ${val.status}`}>
                <span class="status-name">{key}</span>
                <span class="status-label">{val.status}</span>
                <span class="status-desc">{val.desc}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    ))}

    <section class="lessons-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Lessons Learned</h2>
      
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h3>1. gRPC Wasn't The Answer</h3>
        <p>First version of Nexus tried gRPC for Python interop. It was clean, simple, and <strong>slow</strong>. Every call meant serialization, TCP stack overhead, and copying bytes through the kernel. For AR latency targets, this was death. The gRPC experiment lasted one week.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h3>2. The Python Memory Wall</h3>
        <p>CPython's memory model is fundamentally incompatible with zero-copy sharing:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The GC moves objects whenever it wants</li>
          <li>The allocator can promote/demote memory at any time</li>
          <li>The GIL means even reading from another thread is unsafe</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can't hand Python a memory address and expect it to still point to valid data five seconds later.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h3>3. Architecture Evolves</h3>
        <p>The original Nexus design assumed it could solve the Python problem internally. It couldn't. PyProbe is a prerequisite. Nexus isn't the spine anymore — <strong>PyProbe is</strong>.</p>
        <p>The new dependency chain: <code>PyProbe → PyJX → Nexus → COBALT</code></p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .arch-page {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .arch-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .title {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--cobalt);
    letter-spacing: -2px;
  }

  .bracket { color: var(--text-dim); }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--cobalt);
    margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .intro {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .intro-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .intro-card h2 {
    color: var(--cobalt);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .intro-card p {
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .intro-card strong {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .intro-card code {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    color: var(--cobalt);
  }

  .layers-vis {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .layers-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .layer-block {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr 2fr;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-left: 4px solid;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .layer-range {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .layer-name {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .layer-comps {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .comp-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 2px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .flow-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .flow-diagram {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .flow-step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 40px 80px 40px 80px 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.05);
  }

  .flow-step:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .step-num {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--cobalt);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .step-from, .step-to {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .step-arrow {
    color: var(--cobalt);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .step-desc {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .component-section {
    margin: 3rem 0;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .comp-header {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.03);
  }

  .comp-title {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .comp-title h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--cobalt);
  }

  .layer-badge {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.15);
    border-radius: 2px;
    color: var(--cobalt);
  }

  .status-badge {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  .status-badge.active {
    background: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.15);
    color: var(--success);
  }

  .status-badge.planning {
    background: rgba(255, 170, 0, 0.15);
    color: var(--warning);
  }

  .status-badge.future {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.15);
    color: var(--cobalt);
  }

  .comp-purpose {
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .comp-body {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .problem-box, .solution-box, .insight-box {
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .problem-box {
    background: rgba(255, 51, 102, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 51, 102, 0.2);
  }

  .problem-box h3 {
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .solution-box {
    background: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.2);
  }

  .solution-box h3 {
    color: var(--success);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .insight-box {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .insight-box h3 {
    color: var(--cobalt);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .problem-box p, .solution-box p, .insight-box p {
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .code-box h3 {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .code-box pre {
    background: var(--bg-dark);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .code-box code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .status-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .status-item {
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--bg-dark);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
  }

  .status-item.complete {
    border-color: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.3);
  }

  .status-item.in_progress {
    border-color: rgba(255, 170, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .status-item.alpha {
    border-color: rgba(255, 170, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .status-item.planned, .status-item.future {
    border-color: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.2);
  }

  .status-item .status-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .status-item .status-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .status-item.complete .status-label {
    background: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.15);
    color: var(--success);
  }

  .status-item.in_progress .status-label, .status-item.alpha .status-label {
    background: rgba(255, 170, 0, 0.15);
    color: var(--warning);
  }

  .status-item.planned .status-label, .status-item.future .status-label {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.15);
    color: var(--cobalt);
  }

  .status-item .status-desc {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .lessons-section {
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .lesson-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lesson-card h3 {
    color: var(--cobalt);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lesson-card p {
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .lesson-card ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .lesson-card li {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .lesson-card code {
    background: rgba(0, 212, 255, 0.1);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    color: var(--cobalt);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .layer-block {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .flow-step {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>